{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QhQ9JqWiFKDN5XptH1Rb1D","type":"tool_result","content":"1130\t * Function:    H5LTget_dataset_info\n1131\t *\n1132\t * Purpose:     Gets information about a dataset.\n1133\t *\n1134\t * Return:      Success: 0, Failure: -1\n1135\t *-------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1136\t */\n1137\t\n1138\therr_t\n1139\tH5LTget_dataset_info(hid_t loc_id, const char *dset_name, hsize_t *dims, H5T_class_t *type_class,\n1140\t                     size_t *type_size)\n1141\t{\n1142\t    hid_t did = -1;\n1143\t    hid_t tid = -1;\n1144\t    hid_t sid = -1;\n1145\t\n1146\t    /* check the arguments */\n1147\t    if (dset_name == NULL)\n1148\t        return -1;\n1149\t\n1150\t    /* open the dataset. */\n1151\t    if ((did = H5Dopen2(loc_id, dset_name, H5P_DEFAULT)) < 0)\n1152\t        return -1;\n1153\t\n1154\t    /* get an identifier for the datatype. */\n1155\t    tid = H5Dget_type(did);\n1156\t\n1157\t    /* get the class. */\n1158\t    if (type_class != NULL)\n1159\t        *type_class = H5Tget_class(tid);\n1160\t\n1161\t    /* get the size. */\n1162\t    if (type_size != NULL)\n1163\t        *type_size = H5Tget_size(tid);\n1164\t\n1165\t    if (dims != NULL) {\n1166\t        /* get the dataspace handle */\n1167\t        if ((sid = H5Dget_space(did)) < 0)\n1168\t            goto out;\n1169\t\n1170\t        /* get dimensions */\n1171\t        if (H5Sget_simple_extent_dims(sid, dims, NULL) < 0)\n1172\t            goto out;\n1173\t\n1174\t        /* terminate access to the dataspace */\n1175\t        if (H5Sclose(sid) < 0)\n1176\t            goto out;\n1177\t    } /* end if */\n1178\t\n1179\t    /* release the datatype. */\n1180\t    if (H5Tclose(tid))\n1181\t        return -1;\n1182\t\n1183\t    /* end access to the dataset */\n1184\t    if (H5Dclose(did))\n1185\t        return -1;\n1186\t\n1187\t    return 0;\n1188\t\n1189\tout:\n1190\t    H5E_BEGIN_TRY\n1191\t    {\n1192\t        H5Tclose(tid);\n1193\t        H5Sclose(sid);\n1194\t        H5Dclose(did);\n1195\t    }\n1196\t    H5E_END_TRY\n1197\t    return -1;\n1198\t}\n1199\t\n1200\t/*-------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1201\t * Function: find_dataset\n1202\t *\n1203\t * Purpose: operator function used by H5LTfind_dataset\n1204\t *\n1205\t * Comments:\n1206\t *\n1207\t *-------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1208\t */\n1209\t\n1210\tstatic herr_t\n1211\tfind_dataset(H5_ATTR_UNUSED hid_t loc_id, const char *name, H5_ATTR_UNUSED const H5L_info2_t *linfo,\n1212\t             void *op_data)\n1213\t{\n1214\t    /* Define a default zero value for return. This will cause the iterator to continue if\n1215\t     * the dataset is not found yet.\n1216\t     */\n1217\t    int ret = 0;\n1218\t\n1219\t    /* check the arguments */\n1220\t    if (name == NULL)\n1221\t        return ret;\n1222\t\n1223\t    /* Shut the compiler up */\n1224\t    (void)loc_id;\n1225\t    (void)linfo;\n1226\t\n1227\t    /* Define a positive value for return value if the dataset was found. This will\n1228\t     * cause the iterator to immediately return that positive value,\n1229\t     * indicating short-circuit success\n1230\t     */\n1231\t    if (strcmp(name, (char *)op_data) == 0)\n1232\t        ret = 1;\n1233\t\n1234\t    return ret;\n1235\t}\n1236\t\n1237\t/*-------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1238\t * Function: H5LTfind_dataset\n1239\t *\n1240\t * Purpose:  Inquires if a dataset named dset_name exists attached\n1241\t *           to the object loc_id.\n1242\t *\n1243\t * Return:\n1244\t *     Success: The return value of the first operator that\n1245\t *              returns non-zero, or zero if all members were\n1246\t *              processed with no operator returning non-zero.\n1247\t *\n1248\t *      Failure:    Negative if something goes wrong within the\n1249\t *              library, or the negative value returned by one\n1250\t *              of the operators.\n1251\t *\n1252\t *-------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1253\t */\n1254\t/* H5Literate wants a non-const pointer but we have a const pointer in the API\n1255\t * call. It's safe to ignore this because we control the callback, don't\n1256\t * modify the op_data buffer (i.e.: dset_name) during the traversal, and the\n1257\t * library never modifies that buffer.\n1258\t */\n1259\tH5_WARN_CAST_AWAY_CONST_OFF\n1260\therr_t\n1261\tH5LTfind_dataset(hid_t loc_id, const char *dset_name)\n1262\t{\n1263\t    return H5Literate2(loc_id, H5_INDEX_NAME, H5_ITER_INC, 0, find_dataset, (void *)dset_name);\n1264\t}\n1265\tH5_WARN_CAST_AWAY_CONST_ON\n1266\t\n1267\t/*-------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1268\t *\n1269\t * Set attribute functions\n1270\t *\n1271\t *-------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1272\t */\n1273\t\n1274\t/*-------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1275\t * Function: H5LTset_attribute_string\n1276\t *\n1277\t * Purpose: Creates and writes a string attribute named attr_name and attaches\n1278\t *          it to the object specified by the name obj_name.\n1279\t *"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"78b03bfe-9de1-460b-8747-2e452ecc1588","uuid":"e506e293-02c5-4af9-937e-c2dd21aed8b3","timestamp":"2026-06-06T19:37:30.360Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/work/agent/target-src/hl/src/H5LT.c","content":" * Function:    H5LTget_dataset_info\n *\n * Purpose:     Gets information about a dataset.\n *\n * Return:      Success: 0, Failure: -1\n *-------------------------------------------------------------------------\n */\n\nherr_t\nH5LTget_dataset_info(hid_t loc_id, const char *dset_name, hsize_t *dims, H5T_class_t *type_class,\n                     size_t *type_size)\n{\n    hid_t did = -1;\n    hid_t tid = -1;\n    hid_t sid = -1;\n\n    /* check the arguments */\n    if (dset_name == NULL)\n        return -1;\n\n    /* open the dataset. */\n    if ((did = H5Dopen2(loc_id, dset_name, H5P_DEFAULT)) < 0)\n        return -1;\n\n    /* get an identifier for the datatype. */\n    tid = H5Dget_type(did);\n\n    /* get the class. */\n    if (type_class != NULL)\n        *type_class = H5Tget_class(tid);\n\n    /* get the size. */\n    if (type_size != NULL)\n        *type_size = H5Tget_size(tid);\n\n    if (dims != NULL) {\n        /* get the dataspace handle */\n        if ((sid = H5Dget_space(did)) < 0)\n            goto out;\n\n        /* get dimensions */\n        if (H5Sget_simple_extent_dims(sid, dims, NULL) < 0)\n            goto out;\n\n        /* terminate access to the dataspace */\n        if (H5Sclose(sid) < 0)\n            goto out;\n    } /* end if */\n\n    /* release the datatype. */\n    if (H5Tclose(tid))\n        return -1;\n\n    /* end access to the dataset */\n    if (H5Dclose(did))\n        return -1;\n\n    return 0;\n\nout:\n    H5E_BEGIN_TRY\n    {\n        H5Tclose(tid);\n        H5Sclose(sid);\n        H5Dclose(did);\n    }\n    H5E_END_TRY\n    return -1;\n}\n\n/*-------------------------------------------------------------------------\n * Function: find_dataset\n *\n * Purpose: operator function used by H5LTfind_dataset\n *\n * Comments:\n *\n *-------------------------------------------------------------------------\n */\n\nstatic herr_t\nfind_dataset(H5_ATTR_UNUSED hid_t loc_id, const char *name, H5_ATTR_UNUSED const H5L_info2_t *linfo,\n             void *op_data)\n{\n    /* Define a default zero value for return. This will cause the iterator to continue if\n     * the dataset is not found yet.\n     */\n    int ret = 0;\n\n    /* check the arguments */\n    if (name == NULL)\n        return ret;\n\n    /* Shut the compiler up */\n    (void)loc_id;\n    (void)linfo;\n\n    /* Define a positive value for return value if the dataset was found. This will\n     * cause the iterator to immediately return that positive value,\n     * indicating short-circuit success\n     */\n    if (strcmp(name, (char *)op_data) == 0)\n        ret = 1;\n\n    return ret;\n}\n\n/*-------------------------------------------------------------------------\n * Function: H5LTfind_dataset\n *\n * Purpose:  Inquires if a dataset named dset_name exists attached\n *           to the object loc_id.\n *\n * Return:\n *     Success: The return value of the first operator that\n *              returns non-zero, or zero if all members were\n *              processed with no operator returning non-zero.\n *\n *      Failure:    Negative if something goes wrong within the\n *              library, or the negative value returned by one\n *              of the operators.\n *\n *-------------------------------------------------------------------------\n */\n/* H5Literate wants a non-const pointer but we have a const pointer in the API\n * call. It's safe to ignore this because we control the callback, don't\n * modify the op_data buffer (i.e.: dset_name) during the traversal, and the\n * library never modifies that buffer.\n */\nH5_WARN_CAST_AWAY_CONST_OFF\nherr_t\nH5LTfind_dataset(hid_t loc_id, const char *dset_name)\n{\n    return H5Literate2(loc_id, H5_INDEX_NAME, H5_ITER_INC, 0, find_dataset, (void *)dset_name);\n}\nH5_WARN_CAST_AWAY_CONST_ON\n\n/*-------------------------------------------------------------------------\n *\n * Set attribute functions\n *\n *-------------------------------------------------------------------------\n */\n\n/*-------------------------------------------------------------------------\n * Function: H5LTset_attribute_string\n *\n * Purpose: Creates and writes a string attribute named attr_name and attaches\n *          it to the object specified by the name obj_name.\n *","numLines":150,"startLine":1130,"totalLines":3520}}}
