{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TcuoALpeTCNccSpDR1MZS6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Build is green (retcode=0). Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Harness: `h5_hlt_fuzzer`**\n\nThe harness exercises the H5LT API the way a real caller would:\n\n1. **`H5LTopen_file_image`** — opens the raw fuzz bytes as a read-only in-memory HDF5 file, exercising the HL image-open code path without disk I/O.\n\n2. **Dataset discovery** — uses `H5Literate2` to find actual dataset names inside the (potentially malformed) file, then augments with 8 hard-coded names to exercise \"not-found\" paths.\n\n3. **Per-dataset pipeline** (correct caller sequence):\n   - `H5LTfind_dataset` — existence check (exercises `H5Literate2` internally)\n   - `H5LTget_dataset_ndims` — get rank (guards against out-of-range values)\n   - `H5LTget_dataset_info` — get dims, type class, type size\n   - `H5LTread_dataset` — only if `total_elements × sizeof(int) ≤ 4 MiB`, with overflow-safe element counting; uses `H5T_NATIVE_INT` for the memory type (HDF5 handles conversion)\n\n4. **Attribute pipeline** — for 10 known attribute names on each dataset and on the root group:\n   - `H5LTfind_attribute` — existence check\n   - `H5LTget_attribute_info` — query type class and size before any read\n   - `H5LTget_attribute_string` — only for string-class attributes with `type_size ≤ 64 KiB`, with a correctly sized `calloc`'d buffer\n\nThe build links `libhdf5_hl.a` (before `libhdf5.a`) and includes `-I/src/hdf5/hl/src` for the `hdf5_hl.h` header. A seed corpus of 54 real HDF5 test files is zipped as `h5_hlt_fuzzer_seed_corpus.zip`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":129,"cache_read_input_tokens":85708,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":129,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"78b03bfe-9de1-460b-8747-2e452ecc1588","uuid":"7ac8f7aa-e4cb-44a8-bac8-863f580222a3"}
